'''Note to editors on how to manage collapsibility:'''
*Use <tt>{&#123;<!--
--><includeonly>{{BASEPAGENAME}}</includeonly><noinclude>''Template name''</noinclude>|state=collapsed}}</tt> to show this template in its collapsed (hidden) state.
*Use <tt>{&#123;<!--
--><includeonly>{{BASEPAGENAME}}</includeonly><noinclude>''Template name''</noinclude>|state=expanded}}</tt> to show this template in its expanded (fully visible) state.
*Use <tt>{&#123;<!--
--><includeonly>{{BASEPAGENAME}}</includeonly><noinclude>''Template name''</noinclude>|state=autocollapse}}</tt> to show this template in its collapsed (hidden) state '''only if''' there is another template of the same type on the page. ({{{state|This}}} is usually the default.)<noinclude>
